Github is useful for many things like organizing projects and collaborating with others. Another use is as a way to organize a portfolio for work. I could use Github as a place to have all of the projects I've worked on in the past. I could use it to give people quick and easy access to the projects I've done so that I would have a way for my employer to see the projects I've done so that they don't just have to take my word for what I have done. Github would also be useful when setting up a portfolio website. I could link to my Github page really easily and they could access all that I have sone from there. Github will also display my ability to work with others colaborating on a single projects which is often done in a lot of different workplaces. In summary, Github creates a convienient and easy place to store the projects I've worked on and also display my ability to collaborate with others. 